  "prompt": "What is the best time of day to drink a single coffee to keep you going for the longest duration?",
  "response": "The best time of day to drink a single coffee to maximize its effects can vary based on individual factors such as caffeine tolerance, sleep patterns, and daily schedules. However, generally speaking, to leverage the natural cortisol rhythm in our bodies, it's often recommended to consume coffee between 9:30 a.m. and 11:30 a.m. Here\u2019s why:\n\n1. **Cortisol levels:** Cortisol is a hormone that helps regulate energy, and it naturally peaks shortly after waking up (around 6:00 - 8:00 a.m.). Consuming coffee during this time might not be as effective because your body is already alert. Once cortisol levels start to dip (mid-morning), caffeine can be more effective.\n\n2. **Afternoon energy dip:** Drinking coffee in the late morning can also help counteract the common energy slump in the early to mid-afternoon. \n\n3. **Avoiding late-day caffeine:** Having coffee too late in the day can impact sleep quality. It's typically best to avoid caffeine at least 6 hours before bedtime.\n\nDepending on your personal routine and sensitivity to caffeine, you might need to adjust this timing. It's also important to stay hydrated, manage stress, and ensure that your overall lifestyle supports your energy needs throughout the day.",
